My team has begun using pathplanner this season for autonomous and we’ve struggled with using the registerCommand(), we have, for example NamedCommands.registerCommand("collect", intake.Collect()) just like int he documentation, but it tells us Collect is undefined for tyke Intake, but its that way int he documentation, does anybody know how to fix it? intake is a valid declaration of the Intake subsystem and Collect is a valid command. We’re using command based programming

When you say NamedCommands.registerCommand("collect", intake.Collect()) this means that Collect is a method on the intake subsystem class that returns a command. It’s hard to say how to fix your code without seeing the rest of it, but you might have meant to say new Collect(intake) or intake.collect().

does the intake.Collect() function return a command or is that just a function. If it is a function then try this:

subsystem.run(intake::Collect);
or
intake.run(intake::Collect);

subsystem being a reference to your intake subsystem singleton created on init.
